---
description: Project-wide AI session rules (process and pointers)
alwaysApply: true
---

All **process** standards for this project live in **`docs/ai-context.md`**. Load and follow it at the start of every session.

**Documentation as source of truth:** **`docs/design/`** (and published docs site, if any) specifies product and system behavior; **`docs/ai-context.md`** specifies AI dev process. Details: **`.cursor/rules/docs-authority-and-escalation.mdc`**.

**Covers:** session bootstrap, **git worktrees** under `.worktrees/FR-NNNN-<slug>/` (feature worktree plus feature-prefixed ticket/stage branch worktrees), **`tasks/ticket-progress.md`** beacon, per-feature **`tasks/feature-history/FR-NNNN-<slug>/tickets.md`**, global DAG index **`docs/design/tickets-initial.md`**, documentation authority and escalation tags, **subagents ahead of large work**, ticket phases (**TEST / DEV / VAL**), and git hygiene (commit, push, PR) per team policy.

**Feature workflow (compose, do not fork):** **`feature-request`** / **`/feature-request`** (design → **`tickets.md`**), then **`identify-frontier`** / **`develop-frontier`** / **`finish-feature`** (default) or **`finish-frontier`** on the **global** ticket graph — see **`docs/ai-context.md` §2b–§2d**. **`/commit-with-metrics`** is optional for commits.

**Doc sync:** When you change Cursor rules, skills, or Claude commands together, follow **`.cursor/rules/cursor-claude-doc-sync.mdc`**.

**Stack-specific code style:** enable **`.cursor/rules/stack-conventions.mdc`** when you have chosen a stack (set `alwaysApply: true` in that file).

**Claude Code** without Cursor: mirror expectations in **`.claude/rules/development-standards.md`** and slash commands under **`.claude/commands/`**.
